Insecurity is rising in Tudor, where boda boda operators say thugs rob them of money and motorcycles. Some of us have been injured, operator Solomon Munyoki said.They said police are slow to respond whenever a crime is reported. In six months, 10 motorcycles have been stolen, they said.Mvita MP aspirant Omar Shalloh urged police to secure the area. He said the operators, who only earn a little money, are also targeted by unscrupulous officers manning the Nyali Bridge and demanding money.